Minister of Justice and Correctional Services, Ronald Lamola will brief media on the outcomes of the Cabinet meeting held on Wednesday, 05 August 2020. PRETORIA - Minister of Justice and Correctional Services Ronald Lamola will brief media on the outcomes of the Cabinet meeting held on Wednesday. President Cyril Ramaphosa on Thursday appointed several ministers to investigate the alleged looting of millions through dodgy PPE tenders. READ: Ramaphosa orders PPE fraud probe Lamola will chair the committee. Ramaphosa has been battling to explain why his cabinet and NEC members scored the lucrative contracts.